-- Peru Stocks: Maple, Panoro, Rio Alto, Pacasmayo, Southern Copper
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-01-09T18:51:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-09/peru-stocks-maple-panoro-rio-alto-pacasmayo-southern-copper.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:18 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose 0.4 percent to 19,870.15. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  climbed 0.2 percent to 2,548.98.  Industrial and mining stocks gained as investors bet
fourth-quarter earnings will beat forecasts, said Leoncio Altamirano, a trader at Lima-based Juan Magot y Asociados SAB.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian exploration
company, climbed 5.1 percent to 41 cents.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas producer with operations in Peru,
rose 4.4 percent to $1.18.  Grana y Montero SA (GRAMONC1)  (GRAMONC1 PE),
Peru’s largest construction firm, gained 3.2 percent to 6.50
soles.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a gold producer, rose for
a sixth session, adding 2 percent to $3.60.  Cementos Pacasmayo
SAA (CPACASC1)  (CPACASC1 PE), the Hochschild Group’s cement producer, rose
1.8 percent to 5.75 soles after disclosing plans for a $250
million American depositary receipt issue.  Southern Copper Corp. (PCU\C)  (SCCO PE), the country’s biggest
producer of the metal, fell for a fourth day, sliding 1.6
percent to $30.50 after copper declined in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
